Here is the Python code to create a scatter plot of x vs y colored by category:

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Set publication-quality style
plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')

# Create the figure and axis
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

# Scatter plot with color based on category
ax.scatter(df['x'], df['y'], c=pd.Categorical(df['category']).codes)

# Add title and labels
ax.set_title('Scatter Plot of x vs y Colored by Category')
ax.set_xlabel('x')
ax.set_ylabel('y')

# Show the plot (comment out plt.show() if you don't want to display)
```
